Week 1: Assignment Command Line
CLI Exercises:
Command Line:
1. List how many files (hidden files included) are there in your home directory
2. List how many directories (hidden dirs included) are there in your home directory
3. List all files/directories starting with letter “D” in your home directory
4. Change permissions to a text file by giving read-write access to owners and groups only.
5. Find out which processes are taking up maximum CPU
6. Find out which processes are taking up more memory
7. Copy a text file from home directory to “tmp” directory
8. Given a text file, employee.txt, find out the following
9. List all employee ids, names and role whose name starts with “J”
10. List all fields, sorted by name in ascending order whose department is “Technology” and write them into emp.txt
11. List name and salaries of employees who work in “Technology” department as a “Sysadmin” and overwrite emp.txt
12. Calculate the average salary of all employees
13. List the distinct departments in the organisation.
14. Count the number of employees who are developers
15. Print the distinct salaries of employees without $ sign


OS:
1. Find out how to determine the OS architecture? (Is it 32 bit or 64 bit)
2. How to shutdown the OS from the command line.
3. Find out what shell you are using.
4. Find out which processes are taking more memory from the command line ?
5. How do you terminate one process from the command line ?
6. What is a symlink ? And how do you create one ?

Networking:
Learn the following commands(in linux) and their respective uses
1. ping.
2. nslookup.
3. command to find ip address and mac id of the interface
4. find the hostname of the machine.

Employee.txt(input file)
100  Thomas  Manager    Sales       $5,000
200  Jason   Developer  Technology  $5,500
300  Sanjay  Sysadmin   Technology  $7,000
400  Nisha   Manager    Marketing   $9,500
500  Randy   DBA        Technology  $6,000
600  Jonny	 Developer  Technology  $7,000
700  Thomas  Sysadmin   Marketing   $6,000 (edited) 





Week 1: Wallet Assignment - TDD
Requirement 1: As a wallet owner, I would like to be able to put money into my wallet so that I can take it out later.
Requirement 2: As a wallet owner, I would like to be able to take a specified amount of money out of the wallet.
Requirement 3:
As a wallet owner,
I want to know the total money my wallet has for the preferred currency
Given preferred currency is Rs.,
When my wallet has Rs.50 & $1
Then the sum of money in the wallet is Rs.124.85
Given Preferred currency is $
When my wallet has Rs.74.85, $1, Rs.149.7
Then sum of money in the wallet is $4 (edited) 
